Inverness defender Josh Meekings was retrospectively suspended for handball against Celtic in the Scottish Cup semi-final . 
  FIFA vice-president Jim Boyce says the SFA are 'entirely wrong' to ban him from the final . 
  Inverness are appealing the one-match suspension . 
  Meeking was charged over the handball that denied Celtic a goal . 
  He would have been banned for one game if he was sent off . 
 